## Key Differences Recap: Azure Load Balancer vs Application Gateway  
(Relevant to Envoy Gateway / Standard LB Setup on AKS)

| Aspect                        | Azure Load Balancer (L4, Envoy Gateway setup)          | Azure Application Gateway (L7)                              |
|-------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| Connection Handling           | Forwards original connection (DNAT dest only)          | Terminates client conn, creates new connection to backend   |
| Source IP at Backend          | Original client public IP (preserved)                  | Application Gateway instance private IP                     |
| Destination at Backend        | Backend private IP (after DNAT)                        | Backend private IP (direct)                                 |
| NAT Type (Inbound to Backend) | DNAT (public → private destination)                    | No DNAT – new connection uses private IPs directly          |
| SNAT on Backend Leg           | No (inbound)                                           | No – uses own private IP as source naturally                |
| "Conversion" Method           | Packet-level NAT (preserves original flow)             | Full proxy + new connection                                 |
| Client IP Visibility at Backend | Direct (source IP)                                   | Via `X-Forwarded-For` HTTP header only                      |
| NSG Sees Traffic as...        | From public internet (client IP)                       | From internal VNet (App GW subnet private IP)               |
| Why It Reaches Backend        | Default `AzureLoadBalancer` rule allows it             | Intra-VNet default allow (or explicit from App GW subnet)   |
| Typical NSG Rule Needed       | Allow from `AzureLoadBalancer` service tag             | Allow from Application Gateway subnet CIDR (if restricted)  |
| Layer 7 Features              | None (no HTTP awareness)                               | URL/path routing, WAF, SSL termination, header rewrite      |
| Use Case in AKS               | Public LoadBalancer Service (e.g., Envoy Gateway)      | Advanced ingress with WAF, routing, TLS offload             |
